This is a key condition set by the United States (US) for Sudan to be removed from a terrorism blacklist. It is not clear how much Khartoum will pay. Al-Qaeda said it had carried out the attack in which the warship was rammed by a rubber dinghy packed with explosives. The US ruled Sudan was responsible because the two suicide bombers were trained in the country, an allegation denied by Khartoum.

--BBC--